Job Number: 1946395 Business: GE Energy Management Business Segment: EM-DE Digital Energy About Us: GE (NYSE: GE) works on things that matter. The best people and the best technologies taking on the toughest challenges. Finding solutions in energy, health and home, transportation and finance. Building, powering, moving and curing the world. Not just imagining. Doing. GE works. For more information, visit the company's website at www.ge.com Posted Position Title: Field Service Application Engineer Career Level: Experienced Function: Services Function Segment: Field Services Location: United Arab Emirates U.S. State, China or Canada Provinces: City: Abu Dhabi Postal Code: Relocation Assistance: No Role Summary/Purpose: Reporting directly to the Field Service Manager, the Field Service Application Engineer is a key member of the Grid Automation Service team, providing Application Engineering support both internally and externally and conducting Field Service activities at Protection & Control integrators and end customer facilities. Essential Responsibilities: - Commissioning activities for Protection & Control and Substation Automation Systems.- Configuration of Protection Relays, Control Units, Gateways, SCADAs and Ethernet switches.- Training to customers.- Engineering for Protection & Control panels and Integrated Systems.- EHS Leadership, conduct field work in compliance with applicable regulations and encourage accurate employee safety practices.- Act as a primary technical resource for on-site work and lead resolving engineering and product issues. Providing technical direction to skilled labour while performing work on customer sites and equipment to assure the executed work reflects the quality standards and attention to detail that maintains a professional image for the customer and company.- Provide installation and service direction on-site and remotely.- Liaise effectively with customers in job planning, execution, follow-up and sales support, and internally with engineering departments, manufacturing, and Sales team.- Provide both external and internal timely, accurate, professional reports.- Provide, audit, and implement quality control requirements for on-site activities.- Communicate schedule details, project milestones, manpower requirements, quality issues, and tools/equipment requirements to the appropriate individuals.- Leverage applicable Lean/6-Sigma projects.- Work closely with the Grid Automation Centre of Excellence in Bilbao, Spain.- Support the Sales and Commercial teams. Qualifications/Requirements: - Electronics/Electrical Engineering degree or equivalent.- Experience in O&G;/Energy/Utility Project environments.- Proficiency level in Arab and English. A third language highly valued.- Willingness and ability to travel in ME region (Around 180 days/year).- Excellent interpersonal and communication skills with a strong customer focus and ability to cooperate with the different departments.- A rigorous team working approach, good communication and interpersonal skills with a high level of self-motivation, flexibility and self-learning aptitude.- Ability to prioritize and effectively handle multiple assignments, consistently meeting deadlines.- Experience with electrical Protection relays and Control systems (LV, MV & HV). Additional Eligibility Qualifications:
Desired Characteristics: - Strong technical skills on GE Protection Relays, Communication Protocols, SCADA.- Background in Electrical Control Systems and SCADA/DCS systems.- GE DE P&C; and SAS products and solutions. CCU, GEPower, D20, D25, D200, D400, PLA, F650, UR family, etc.- Experience in Electrical Substation Automation Systems, with a particular emphasis on IEC-61850 based communication systems and Electrical SCADA/HMIs.- Must be a motivator, self-starter and dedicated team player.- Ability to organize, prioritize and achieve milestones and deliverables.- Open to working extended hours if the situation requires.- Sound judgment, level headed under pressure, with an ability to think on feet.- Self-starter with a sense of urgency and an ability to work to tight deadlines.- Excellent verbal and written communication skills.- High interpersonal skills.
